==English==
===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} [[Ήρακλης]] (''Herakles'') meaning "glory of Hera", from [[Hera]] + ''kles'', (glory).

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Heracles'''

# {{greekmyth}}: Son of [[Zeus]] and [[Alcmene]], a celebrated [[hero]] who possessed exceptional [[strength]].  Most famous for his 12 [[labor]]s performed to [[redeem]] himself after killing his family.

